Matwetwe has taken South Africa by a storm, being one of the country's top movies right now. The film had a solid opening weekend, making over 900 thousand in its first three days after being released. Directed, written and produced by Lediga, with a fresh-faced cast led by Tebatso Mashishi and Sibusiso Khwinana has grossed over 2 million rands in it's second week at box office.This is a first for a locally produced movie, which is now sitting at number three on the charts behind international films Aquaman and Bohemian Rhapsody.Among his many talents, South African House music producer and DJ, Black Coffee lends his producing skills as an Executive Producer for Matwetwe.   